= Left-Handed Mouse =
To get a left-handed mouse (that is, to swap the left and right buttons), follow these instructions: <ref>
* Version 18: This solution is applicable to version 18 with Wayland, where input parameters are not yet fully integrated into LXQt.
* Future versions: First try: ''Menu -> Preferences -> Keyboard and Mouse''
</ref>
<br>

{{IconSet|h1|1}} Create the required directory
{{CodeSelect|code=
mkdir --parents ~/.config/labwc
}} <br>

{{IconSet|h1|2}} {{Open File|filename=
~/.config/labwc/rc.xml
}}

{{IconSet|h1|3}} Type in or copy the following lines

<ref>
Source: [https://forums.kicksecure.com/t/how-to-get-a-left-hand-mouse-solved/1560 Kicksecure forums thread: How to get a left-hand mouse (Solved)]
</ref>
{{CodeSelect|code=
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<labwc_config>
  <libinput>
    <device>
      <leftHanded>yes</leftHanded>
    </device>
  </libinput>
</labwc_config>
}}
<br>

{{IconSet|h1|4}} Log out and log in, or reboot.

For the changes to take effect, you must log out and log in, or reboot.

{{IconSet|h1|5}} Done.

The left-handed mouse button mapping has been configured for labwc.

